Default Values:
int sum (int a=0, int b = 0){...}

Order matters, no type-matching

Default Values always start from right to left,

Templates:

char sum (char a, char b) {return a+} // then we repeat exact same thing except change datatype

template <typename T> T sum (T a, T b) {return a+b}...

cout << sum<int>(1,2)<<" "<< sum<float>(2.1f, 3.0f) << endl;

Two Types:

template <typename T> T sum (T a, T b) {return a+b}...

C++20:

auto sum (auto a, auto b) { return a+b;} 
